<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id056eee61-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d" identifier="/us/usc/t19/s1643"><num value="1643">§ 1643.</num><heading> Application of customs reorganization act</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The rights, privileges, powers, and duties vested in or imposed upon the Secretary of the Treasury by this chapter shall be subject to the provisions of subdivision (a) of <ref href="/us/usc/t19/s2073">section 2073 of this title</ref>.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id056eee62-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d">(<ref href="/us/act/1930-06-17/ch497">June 17, 1930, ch. 497</ref>, title IV, § 643, <ref href="/us/stat/46/761">46 Stat. 761</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id056eee63-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id056eee64-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="id056eee65-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">References in Text</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Subdivision (a) of <ref href="/us/usc/t19/s2073">section 2073 of this title</ref>, referred to in text, was repealed by <ref href="/us/act/1954-09-03/ch1263/s10">act Sept. 3, 1954, ch. 1263, § 10</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/68/1229">68 Stat. 1229</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
